[{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-choice-children","title":"IELTS Writing Task 2 Sample Answer: Choice for Children (IELTS Cambridge 12)","prompt":"Some people believe that allowing children to make their own choices on everyday matters (such as food, clothes and entertainment) is likely to result in a society of individuals who only think about their own wishes. Other people believe that it is important for children to make decisions about matters that affect them. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-populations-young-people-cambridge-12","title":"IELTS Writing Task 2 Sample Answer: Populations, Young People (Cambridge 12)","prompt":"At the present time, the population of some countries includes a relatively large number of young adults, compared with the number of older people. Do the advantages of this situation outweigh the disadvantages?","question_type":"advantages_disadvantages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-railway-lines-cambridge-12","title":"IELTS Writing Task 2 Sample Answer: Railway Lines (Cambridge 12)","prompt":"In a number of countries, some people think it is necessary to spend large sums of money on constructing new railway lines for very fast trains between cities. Others believe the money should be spent on improving existing public transport. Discuss both these views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-scientific-research-ielts-cambridge-12","title":"IELTS Writing Task 2 Sample Answer: Scientific Research (IELTS Cambridge 12)","prompt":"Some people believe that it is good to share as much information as possible in scientific research, business, and the academic world. Others believe that some information is too important or too valuable to be shared freely. Discuss both these views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-agriculture-cambridge-ielts-13","title":"IELTS Writing Task 2 Sample Answer: Agriculture (Cambridge IELTS 13)","prompt":"In spite of the advances made in agriculture, many people around the world still go hungry. Why is this the case? What can be done about this problem?","question_type":"causes_solutions","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-choice-ielts-cambridge-13","title":"IELTS Writing Task 2 Sample Answer: Choice (IELTS Cambridge 13)","prompt":"Some people believe that nowadays we have too many choices. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-foreign-languages-cambridge-13","title":"IELTS Writing Task 2 Sample Answer: Foreign Languages (Cambridge 13)","prompt":"Living in a country where you have to speak a foreign language can cause serious social problems, as well as practical problems. To what extent do you agree or disagree with this statement?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-history-cambridge-ielts-13","title":"IELTS Writing Task 2 Sample Answer: History (Cambridge IELTS 13)","prompt":"Some people say history is one of the most important school subjects. Other people think that, in today's world, subjects like science and technology are more important than history. Discuss both these views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-newspapers-media","title":"IELTS Writing Task 2 Sample Answer: Newspapers and Media (Real Test)","prompt":"Some people think that newspapers are the best way to learn news. However, others believe that they can learn news better through other media. Discuss both views and give your opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"5172-2","title":"IELTS Writing Task 2 Sample Answer: Transportation","prompt":"Some people think that governments should invest mainly in making public transportation faster while others think there are more important priorities (cost, the environment). Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"music-bringing-people-together","title":"Music as a Bridge Across Cultures and Ages","prompt":"Some people say that music is a good way of bringing people of different cultures and ages together. To what extent do you agree or disagree with this opinion?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"children-achieve-anything-message","title":"Children and Unlimited Potential Messages","prompt":"In some cultures, children are often told that they can achieve anything if they try hard enough. What are the advantages and disadvantages of giving children this message?","question_type":"advantages_disadvantages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"owning-home-importance-positive-negative","title":"Home Ownership Importance and Its Implications","prompt":"In some countries, owning a home rather than renting one is very important for people. Why might this be the case? Do you think this is a positive or negative situation?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"printed-newspapers-online-reading-future","title":"Future of Printed Newspapers and Online Reading","prompt":"In the future, nobody will buy printed newspapers or books because they will be able to read everything they want online without paying. To what extent do you agree or disagree with this statement?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"advertising-new-products-novelty","title":"Advertising New Products and Marketing Strategy","prompt":"In their advertising, businesses nowadays usually emphasise that their products are new in some way. Why is this? Do you think it is a positive or negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"driverless-vehicles-autonomous-cars","title":"Driverless Vehicles Advantages and Disadvantages","prompt":"In the future all cars, buses and trucks will be driverless. The only people travelling inside these vehicles will be passengers. Do you think the advantages of driverless vehicles outweigh the disadvantages?","question_type":"advantages_disadvantages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"sugar-manufactured-foods-health","title":"Manufactured Foods with High Sugar Content","prompt":"Many manufactured food and drink products contain high levels of sugar, which causes many health problems. Sugary products should be made more expensive to encourage people to consume less sugar. Do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-cambridge-17-essay-health-problems","title":"Health Problems: Alternative Medicines","prompt":"Nowadays, an increasing number of people with health problems are using alternative medicines and treatments instead of visiting their normal doctor. Do you think this is a positive or negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-cambridge-17-essay-professionals","title":"Professionals Working in Their Training Country","prompt":"Some people believe that professionals, such as doctors and engineers, should be required to work in the country where they did their training. Others believe they should be free to work in another country if they wish. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-cambridge-18-living-longer-an-ageing-population","title":"An Ageing Population","prompt":"Around the world, people are now living longer than ever before in the past. Some say an ageing population creates problems for governments. Others believe there are benefits to society having more elderly people. To what extent do the advantages of possessing an ageing population outweigh the disadvantages?","question_type":"advantages_disadvantages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-cambridge-18-the-most-important-aim-of-science","title":"The Most Important Aim of Science","prompt":"The most important aim of science ought to be to improve people's lives. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-cambridge-18-university-students-and-main-subjects","title":"University Students and Main Subjects","prompt":"Many university students want to learn about different subjects in addition to their main subjects. Others feel it is more important to give all their time and attention to studying for their qualification. Discuss both views and give your opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-cambridge-19-essay-competition","title":"Competition at Work, School, and Daily Life","prompt":"Some people think that competition at work, at school and in daily life is a good thing. Others believe that we should try to cooperate more, rather than competing against each other. Discuss both these views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-cambridge-19-essay-save-money-for-the-future","title":"Save Money for the Future","prompt":"It is important for everyone, including young people, to save money for their future. To what extent do you agree or disagree with this statement?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-cambridge-19-essay-supermarkets","title":"Supermarkets and Global Food Production","prompt":"In many countries nowadays, consumers can go to a supermarket and buy food produced all over the world. Do you think this is a positive or negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-cambridge-20-essay-global-fashion-trends","title":"IELTS Cambridge 20 Essay: Global Fashion Trends","prompt":"Many aspects of the way people dress today are influenced by global fashion trends. How has global fashion become such a strong influence on people's lives? Do you think this is a positive or negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-cambridge-20-essay-stopping-flying","title":"IELTS Essay: Stopping Flying","prompt":"Some groups of people have decided to reduce the number of times they fly every year or to stop flying altogether. Do you think that the environmental benefits of this development outweigh the disadvantages for individuals and businesses?","question_type":"advantages_disadvantages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"cambridge-16-ielts-essay-best-time-history-general-training","title":"Cambridge 16 IELTS Essay: The Best Time in History","prompt":"Some people believe that now is the best time in history to be alive, while others argue that life was better in the past. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-general-training-children-sports","title":"IELTS Essay General Training: Children and Sports","prompt":"Some people believe that children should do sports so that they will grow up as healthy adults, but others feel sports are just about enjoying yourself. Discuss these both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-general-training-cities","title":"IELTS Essay General Training: Cities vs Rural Areas","prompt":"Some people think that cities are the best places to live. Others prefer to live in rural areas. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-general-training-cooking-at-home","title":"IELTS Essay General Training: Cooking at Home","prompt":"Cooking at home is a waste of time because there are so many convenient fast food options that make life less stressful. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-general-training-fast-foods-effect-on-lifestyle-and-diet","title":"IELTS Essay General Training: Fast Food's Effect on Lifestyle and Diet","prompt":"Fast food has become more common in recent years. Some people think that it has a negative effect on lifestyles and diets. Do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-supermarkets","title":"IELTS Essay General Training: Supermarkets and Small Shops","prompt":"Many large supermarkets are being built today while the number of small shops is decreasing. Do the advantages of this outweigh the disadvantages?","question_type":"advantages_disadvantages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"wild-animals-zoos","title":"Wild Animals and Zoos","prompt":"Some people believe that wild animals should not be kept in zoos or other man-made environments as there is no longer a need for them in the 21st century. Do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"behaviour-abroad","title":"Behaviour Abroad","prompt":"There are different customs in different countries related to how people eat, dress, and so on. Some think that people visiting a country should behave according to customs of the country they visit. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"children-farming","title":"Children Farming","prompt":"It is sometimes suggested that primary schoolchildren should learn how to grow vegetables and keep animals. Do you think that the advantages of this outweigh the disadvantages?","question_type":"advantages_disadvantages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"children-visiting-museums","title":"Children Visiting Museums","prompt":"Some people think that children can learn about history by visiting museums, while others feel that there are better ways to learn about history. Discuss both views and give your opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"children-phones","title":"Children on Their Phones","prompt":"Some children spend hours every day on their smartphones. Why is this the case? Do you think this is a positive or a negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"choosing-a-job","title":"Choosing a Job","prompt":"Some people say young people should be completely free to choose their future job but others think young people must be more realistic in their choice. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-fuel-costs","title":"IELTS Essay: Fuel Costs","prompt":"The best way to solve the world's environmental problems is to increase the cost of fuel for cars and other private vehicles. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-hard-work","title":"IELTS Essay: Hard Work","prompt":"Some people work harder than others. Why is this? Is this a positive or negative habit?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-having-children-later","title":"IELTS Essay: Having Children Later","prompt":"Having Children Later Many people nowadays tend to marry and have children in their thirties rather than at a younger age. Is this a positive or negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-healthy-lifestyles-in-the-countryside","title":"IELTS Essay: Healthy Lifestyles in the Countryside","prompt":"Many people believe that it is easier to have a healthy lifestyle in the countryside. Other believe that there are health benefits to living in cities. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-hot-cold-climates","title":"IELTS Essay: Hot and Cold Climates","prompt":"Some people prefer activities and lifestyles in hot climates while others prefer living in cold climates. Discuss both views and give your opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-influence-ads","title":"IELTS Essay: Influence of Ads","prompt":"Consumers are faced with increasing numbers of advertisements from competing companies. To what extent do you think are consumers are influenced by advertisements? What measures can be taken to protect them?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"moving-places","title":"Moving to Different Places","prompt":"Some people are happy to stay in the same area for their whole life, while others prefer living in many different places. Discuss both views and give your opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"nurses-qualities","title":"Nurses and Required Qualities","prompt":"Nowadays nurses should not just be required to do basic training but they must have other qualities as well to do their jobs well. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"recycling-school","title":"Teaching Recycling at School","prompt":"Some say that children should be taught at school to recycle and avoid waste. Others say they should learn this at home. Discuss both views and give your opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"retirement-homes-communities","title":"Retirement Homes and Older People","prompt":"Nowadays some older people choose to live in retirement communities and centers with other people, rather than living with their adult children. Is this a positive or negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-essay-practical-skills","title":"Practical Skills in School","prompt":"Many feel that students today should learn practical skills at school such as car maintenance and managing a bank account. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-essay-international-sporting-events","title":"International Sporting Events","prompt":"One good way to promote world peace is through international sporting events. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-essay-modern-electronics-real-past-ielts-exam","title":"Modern Electronics","prompt":"Some old people today struggle with the use of modern technologies such as smartphones and computers. What is the cause of this? What are some possible solutions?","question_type":"causes_solutions","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-general-training-dying-languages","title":"Dying Languages","prompt":"Many local languages today are dying out due to the rise of languages like English. Is this a positive or negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-general-training-fame","title":"Fame","prompt":"Due to television and the internet it is easier today for a large number of people to become famous. Is this a positive or negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-general-training","title":"Gym and Exercise","prompt":"Many feel that going to the gym is the best way to stay fit. Others think there are more effective methods. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"recent-general-training-ielts-writing-topics-2022","title":"Working Hours Legislation","prompt":"Some countries have introduced laws to limit the working hours that an employer can ask from an employee. Why are these laws introduced? What is your opinion? Is this a positive or negative trend?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-task-2-sample-answer-business","title":"Online Business Meetings and Training","prompt":"Recent research has shown that business meetings and training are increasingly taking place online. What are the advantages and disadvantages of this?","question_type":"advantages_disadvantages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-climate-change","title":"Individual vs. Corporate Responsibility for Climate Change","prompt":"Climate change is a phenomenon that affects countries all over the world. Many people strongly believe that it is the responsibility of individuals, rather than corporations and governments, to deal with this problem. To what extent do you agree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-leadership","title":"Natural vs. Learned Leadership Skills","prompt":"Some are of the opinion that people are naturally born as good leaders while others feel that leadership skills can be learned. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-literature","title":"National vs. International Literature in Education","prompt":"Some people say that school children should be mainly taught about the literature (e.g fiction and poetry) of their own country because it is more important than that of other countries. To what extent do you agree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"writing-task-2-ielts-sample-answer-museums","title":"Museum Collections: National vs. International Focus","prompt":"Museums and art galleries should focus on works that show the history and culture of their own country rather than works of other parts of the world. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-overpopulation","title":"Relocating Businesses to Solve Urban Problems","prompt":"Traffic and housing problems in major cities could be solved by moving companies, factories and their employees to the countryside. Do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-plastic-bags","title":"Banning Plastic Shopping Bags","prompt":"Plastic shopping bags are used widely and cause many environmental problems. Some people say they should be banned. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-world-cup-olympics","title":"Major Sporting Events: Waste of Money or Economic Benefit","prompt":"Some people think that it is a waste of money for countries to host big sporting events like the world cup, and that the money would be better spent on other things. However, others think that hosting large sporting events has a clear, positive impact on a country. Discuss both these views and give your opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-general-training-strict-teachers","title":"Strict vs. Friendly Teachers","prompt":"Some people believe that teacher should be strict in order to best motivate students while others say that friendly teachers are more important. Discuss both sides and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-activities-for-leisure-time","title":"Activities for Leisure Time","prompt":"Some people think that one should plan in detail activities for their leisure time, while others disagree with this view. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-advertising-children","title":"Advertising to Children","prompt":"In some countries, there has been an increase in the number of advertisements which try to persuade children to buy snacks, toys, and other goods. Parents often claim that these ads are unfair. Discuss both views and give your opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-advertising","title":"Advertising","prompt":"Some feel that the effects of advertising are positive for individuals and businesses, while others think they are negative. Discuss both sides and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-advice-for-medical-problems","title":"Advice for Medical Problems","prompt":"Some people today prefer to get advice for medical problems and do not want to visit a doctor. Why is this? Is this a positive or a negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-animals","title":"Animals","prompt":"Many believe that it is important to protect all wild animals, while others think that it is important to protect some, not all of them. Discuss both views and give your opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-athletes-as-role-models","title":"Athletes as Role Models","prompt":"Some people believe that professional athletes serve as positive role models for young people, while others argue that their behavior both on and off the field has a negative influence. Discuss both sides and give your opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-attention-spans","title":"Attention Spans","prompt":"Many today feel that attention spans are becoming shorter due to the prevalence of social media. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-ban-advertising","title":"Ban Advertising","prompt":"Some people think that there should be a complete ban on all forms of advertising. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-bicycles","title":"Bicycles","prompt":"Some people say that the bicycles are a good, modern means of transportation. Other say riding a bicycle has clear disadvantages. Discuss both view points and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-breaking-traffic-laws","title":"Breaking Traffic Laws","prompt":"Not all drivers obey the laws while driving on roads. What are the reasons for this? What can be done to fix this problem?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-competition-university","title":"IELTS Essay: Competition in University","prompt":"Competition for university study is becoming increasingly strong. Why are universities becoming more competitive? Why is this a positive or negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-competitiveness-men-women","title":"IELTS Essay: Competitiveness for Men & Women","prompt":"Some claim that men are naturally more competitive than women. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-compulsory-math-philosophy","title":"IELTS Essay: Compulsory Math and Philosophy","prompt":"Some people think that because children find subjects such as mathematics and philosophy difficult, they ought to be optional instead of compulsory. To what extent do you agree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-computer-games","title":"IELTS Essay: Computer Games","prompt":"Computer games are very popular for all ages and nationalities. Parents think this has little educational value and it will be harmful for children. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-computer-games-2","title":"IELTS Essay: Computer Games","prompt":"Many adults nowadays prefer spending their free time playing computer games. Why do they do this? Is this a positive or negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-convenience-foods","title":"IELTS Essay: Convenience Foods","prompt":"Convenience foods will become increasingly prevalent and eventually replace traditional foods and methods of preparation. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-copying","title":"IELTS Essay: Copying","prompt":"The tendency of human beings to copy one another is shown in the popularity of areas such as fashion and consumer goods. To what extent do you agree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-creativity","title":"IELTS Essay: Creativity","prompt":"Doing an enjoyable activity with a child can is better for their overall skills development and creativity than reading. To what extent do you agree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-credit-cards","title":"IELTS Essay: Credit Cards","prompt":"Nowadays, it is easier for young people to have a credit card compared to the past. Do the advantages of this trend outweigh the disadvantages?","question_type":"advantages_disadvantages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-crime-rates-technological-prevention","title":"Crime Rates and Technological Prevention","prompt":"Crime rates will fall as advances in technology make it easier to detect and prevent crimes. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-crime-technology","title":"Crime and Technology","prompt":"Some people think technology development decreases crime, while others believe it actually encourages crime. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-crime-and-human-nature","title":"Crime and Human Nature","prompt":"Many researchers believe that we can now study the behaviour of children to see if they will grow up to be criminals, while others disagree. To what extent do you think crime is determined by genetics? Is it possible to stop children from growing up to be criminals?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-criminal-treatment","title":"Criminal Treatment","prompt":"Young people committing crimes should be treated the same as adults by the authorities. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-curfews","title":"Curfews","prompt":"Some countries are considering imposing curfews in which teenagers will not be allowed outdoors at night unless they are accompanied by an adult. To what extent do you agree or disagree with this policy?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-cyclists","title":"Cyclists","prompt":"Some experts say for road safety cyclists should pass a test before being allowed on public roads. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-declining-animals","title":"Declining Animals","prompt":"In many countries, the number of animals and plants is declining. Why do you think this is happening? How can this issue be solved?","question_type":"causes_solutions","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-dependent-and-independent-individuals","title":"IELTS Essay: Dependent and Independent Individuals","prompt":"Some people think that individuals today are more dependent on each other. Others believe people have become more independent. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-doctors-recommendations","title":"IELTS Essay: Doctors' Recommendations","prompt":"Many doctors recommend that older people exercise regularly, but most patients do not follow an exercise routine. Why do you think this happens? How can people be encouraged to exercise regularly?","question_type":"causes_solutions","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-drilling","title":"IELTS Essay: Drilling","prompt":"In recent years, there has been a significant increase in the number of oil drilling operations in remote locations around the world. This has brought economic benefits to some countries, though it has also raised concerns about the environmental impact of these operations. Discuss both sides and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-driving-tests","title":"IELTS Essay: Driving Tests","prompt":"Driving tests are important for ensuring road safety and reducing accidents. Some argue that current driving test standards are too lenient, while others believe they are adequately challenging. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-early-language-learning","title":"IELTS Essay: Early Language Learning","prompt":"Some believe that students should begin learning a language very early in school while others think these subjects should be taught later. Discuss both sides and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-economic-progress","title":"IELTS Essay: Economic Progress","prompt":"Many governments think that economic progress is their most important goal. Some people, however, think that other types of progress are equally important for a country. Discuss both these views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-education-as-a-basic-right","title":"IELTS Essay: Education as a Basic Right","prompt":"Since university education is seen as a basic right, some people believe the government should make it free for all, regardless of each students's economic status. Do you agree or disagree with this belief?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-education-in-prison","title":"IELTS Essay: Education in Prison","prompt":"Studies show that crime rates are lower among those with educational degrees. Therefore, the best way to reduce the crime rate is to educate criminals while they are still in prison. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-educational-institutions","title":"IELTS Essay: Educational Institutions","prompt":"Many educational institutions give greater importance to subjects related to science and ignore subjects such as drama and literature. Why is this? Is this a positive or negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-extinction","title":"Extinction and Species Loss","prompt":"It is a natural process for animal species to become extinct (e.g. dinosaurs, dodos, etc.). There is no reason why people should try to prevent this from happening. Do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-family-friends","title":"Family and Friends Importance","prompt":"Some people believe that family is more important than friends. To what extent do you agree and disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-family-meals","title":"Family Meals and Eating Together","prompt":"Today family members eat fewer meals together. Why is this? Is this a positive or negative trend?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-farm-animals-vegetables","title":"Farm Animals and Vegetables in Primary School","prompt":"It has been suggested that primary children should learn how to grow vegetables and keep animals. Do the advantages of this outweigh the disadvantages?","question_type":"advantages_disadvantages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-fast-food-families-nutrition-the-environment-5-paragraph-essay","title":"Fast Food and Family Nutrition","prompt":"Many claim that the fast food industry had a negative effect on the environment, eating habits, and families. To what extend do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-fast-food","title":"IELTS Essay: Fast Food","prompt":"Food In many countries, fast food is becoming cheaper and more widely available. Do the disadvantages of this outweigh the advantages?","question_type":"advantages_disadvantages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-financial-matters","title":"IELTS Essay: Financial Matters","prompt":"In numerous nations, there is a growing trend for individuals to frequently discuss financial matters, such as their earnings or expenditures, in everyday conversation. What are the reasons behind this phenomenon? Is it advantageous or detrimental?","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-flights-and-flying","title":"IELTS Essay: Flights and Flying","prompt":"Long distance flight consumes the amount of fuel that a car uses for many years and pollutes the air. Some people think that we should discourage non-essential flights, such as tourists travel, rather than limit the use of cars. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-focus-school","title":"IELTS Essay: Focus at School","prompt":"Many students find it difficult to focus or pay attention at school nowadays. What are the reasons for this? What can be done to solve this problem?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-formal-school-age","title":"IELTS Essay: Formal School Age","prompt":"Some people think that children should begin their formal education at a very early age. Others think they should begin after 7 years of age. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-fossil-fuels-and-alternative-energy","title":"IELTS Essay: Fossil Fuels and Alternative Energy","prompt":"Fossil fuels are the main source of energy around the world today. In some countries, the use of alternative sources of energy is replacing fossil fuels. Is this a positive or negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-free-education","title":"IELTS Essay: Free Education","prompt":"The best way to reduce poverty in developing countries is by giving up to six years of free education, so that they can at least read, write and use numbers. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-free-public-libraries","title":"IELTS Essay: Free Public Libraries","prompt":"Some people think that the government should provide free public libraries in every town, while others think that this is a waste of money because people can access information on the internet. Discuss both viewpoints and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-freedom-to-make-mistakes","title":"IELTS Essay: Freedom to Make Mistakes","prompt":"Some people think children should have the freedom to make mistakes, while other people believe that adults should prevent children from making mistakes. Discuss both sides and give your opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-friendship","title":"IELTS Essay: Friendship","prompt":"Friendships that take place online are not as meaningful as those where people meet each other face to face. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-happiness","title":"IELTS Essay: Happiness","prompt":"Some people think personal happiness is directly related to economic success, while others believe this depends on other factors. Discuss both sides and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-high-school-students","title":"IELTS 