ages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-moving-to-rural-areas","title":"IELTS Essay: Moving to Rural Areas","prompt":"In many cities, problems related to overpopulation are becoming more common. Some governments are now encouraging businesses and individuals to move out of cities to rural areas. Do the advantages of this trend outweigh the disadvantages?","question_type":"advantages_disadvantages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-multinational-companies","title":"IELTS Essay: Multinational Companies","prompt":"The growth of multinational companies and the resulting rise of globalization creates positive effects for all. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-museums-art-galleries","title":"IELTS Essay: Museums and Art Galleries","prompt":"Museums and art galleries should show local history and culture instead of work from different countries. Discuss both views and give opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-music-and-relaxation","title":"IELTS Essay: Music and Relaxation","prompt":"Some people think that the most important function of music is to help people relax. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-musical-instruments","title":"IELTS Essay: Musical Instruments","prompt":"Some educators believe that every child should be taught how to play a musical instrument. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-patriotism-war","title":"IELTS Essay: Patriotism and War","prompt":"Some argue that patriotism is the primary cause of wars globally. Others feel that it serves to prevent less ethical politicians from running a country and starting wars. Discuss both views and give your opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-patriotism","title":"IELTS Essay: Patriotism","prompt":"Some believe patriotism is essential for national unity and social cohesion. Others argue that excessive patriotism creates divisions and international conflict. Discuss both views and give your opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-pay-for-ceos-and-executives","title":"IELTS Essay: Pay for CEOs and Executives","prompt":"Large companies should pay higher salaries to CEOs and executives compared to other workers. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-peer-pressure","title":"IELTS Essay: Peer Pressure","prompt":"Young people are often influenced in their behaviors by others in the same age group. Some argue that peer pressure is important while others feel it has distinct disadvantages. Do the disadvantages of peer pressure outweigh the advantages?","question_type":"advantages_disadvantages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-performance-enhancing-drugs-in-sports","title":"IELTS Essay: Performance-Enhancing Drugs in Sports","prompt":"In recent years, there has been a rise in the use of performance-enhancing drugs in sports. What are the consequences of doping for athletes? What measures should be taken to combat this issue?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-prioritizing-healthcare","title":"IELTS Essay: Prioritizing Healthcare","prompt":"Some feel that governments should prioritize healthcare instead of other important areas. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-private-public-healthcare","title":"IELTS Essay: Private or Public Healthcare","prompt":"Some feel governments, rather than private companies, should be in charge of medical services. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-public-art","title":"IELTS Essay: Public Art","prompt":"Some people believe that the government should spend more money putting in more works of art like paintings and statues in cities to make them better places to live in. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-supermarkets","title":"IELTS Essay: Supermarkets","prompt":"Many supermarkets are selling more and more products that are imported from other countries instead of selling food that is locally sourced. What are the reasons for this? Is this a positive or negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-supporting-artists","title":"IELTS Essay: Supporting Artists","prompt":"Some believe that the government should support artists like musicians, painters, and poets, while others argue that this is a misuse of funds. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-tariffs","title":"IELTS Essay: Tariffs","prompt":"Developing countries should be encouraged to implement high tariffs to grow their local industries. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-the-function-of-music","title":"IELTS Essay: The Function of Music","prompt":"Some argue that music mainly serves as a way for individuals to reduce their stress and anxiety. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-the-internet-and-books","title":"IELTS Essay: The Internet and Books","prompt":"In the past, knowledge was contained in books. Nowadays, knowledge is uploaded to the internet. Do the advantages of this outweigh the disadvantages?","question_type":"advantages_disadvantages","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-essay-the-main-benefit-of-international-cooperation","title":"IELTS Essay: The Main Benefit of International Cooperation","p