nd Corporate Sponsorship","prompt":"Large companies use sports events to promote their products. Some people think this has a negative impact on sports. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-general-training-sample-answer-essay-fashion-real-past-ielts-exam-test","title":"Fashion and Fashionable Clothing","prompt":"The number of people who are interested in and wearing fashionable clothes is increasing. Is this a positive or negative development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-essay-advice-from-old-people","title":"Advice from Old People vs Young People","prompt":"Many people think that it is better to get advice from old rather than young people. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-essay-general-training-school-age","title":"School Age: Leaving at 14 vs 18","prompt":"Some people argue children should stay in school until the age of 18 while others think that 14 years is long enough. Discuss both views and give your opinion.","question_type":"discuss_both_views","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-sample-answer-essay-advertisements-needs","title":"Advertising and Customer Needs","prompt":"Some believe that people will purchase a product based on their needs and advertising is not needed. To what extent do you agree or disagree?","question_type":"agree_disagree","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-entertainers-politicians","title":"IELTS Writing Task 2 Sample Answer Essay: Entertainers & Politicians","prompt":"Nowadays, entertainers get paid more than politicians. What are the reasons for this? Is this a negative or positive development?","question_type":"positive_negative","taskType":"task2"},{"slug":"ielts-writing-task-2-social-media-face-to-face","title":"IELTS Writing Task 2 Sample